<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>10687</id>
	<title>ssi include virtual strangeness</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Hello.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">I am experiencing a strange behaviour from SSI's ``#include virtual''
element/attribute.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">The following piece of HTML/SSI fails to include
(load) the intended html file (header.html), yet it does display the
date (indicating that ssi is working).</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">&lt;!</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">--#include virtual="common/header.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">html" --&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;hello&lt;/h1&gt;
Hello, today is &lt;!</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.4">--#echo var="DATE_LOCAL" --&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;bye&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Besides the error message on the webpage [an error occurred while
processing this directive], there is also a log message sent to
httpd-error.log:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">File does not exist: /u16/ugrad/guide/public_html/common/header.</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.2">htm</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">Yes, the 'l' is missing, whereas it does appear in the file name in
the code above.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="7">
			<sentence id="7.1">I copied common/header.html to common/header.htm, and added some text
to header.htm to distinguish it from header.html.</sentence>
			<sentence id="7.4">Upon reloading the
page (which calls for header.html), the file header.htm is loaded
instead.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="8">
			<sentence id="8.1">My httpd.conf file does not contain .</sentence>
			<sentence id="8.2">htm extensions - only .</sentence>
			<sentence id="8.3">html ones.</sentence>
			<sentence id="8.4">I have the directive XBitHack set to 'on'.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
